The paper deals with the problem of predicting the quality of answers in online health expert question-answering services using machine learning techniques. The proposed framework involves the use of deep belief networks (DBN) to learn high-level hidden semantic representations from physicians' answers. This work involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques and social network analysis, which are typically associated with the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social and information networks (cs.SI), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
